---
title: One-Pan Tortelloni Pesto Gratin with Asparagus and Crispy Panko Breadcrumbs
description: This skillet pasta bake truly is one-pan cooking at its finest— even the sauce thickens in the pan while the tortelloni cook. Although it’s got plenty of creamy, comforting elements, there’s also tons of green in this dish to keep things fresh: asparagus spears are folded in to keep things snappy, while the basil pesto adds an herby touch throughout.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w08-r06-b45e157d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w08-r06-014e7bca.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/w08-r06-5873c3577d69bf53231cfcb2
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 36 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 66 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 29 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1090 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Thinly slice @garlic{4%cloves}. Trim and discard bottom inch from @asparagus{12%ounce}, then cut stalks into 2-inch pieces.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium heat (use an #ovenproof pan{} if you have one). Add asparagus and toss until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add garlic and toss until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @milk{2%box}, @veggie stock concentrate{2} and @pesto{4%ounce} to pan and stir to combine. Add @cheese tortelloni{18%ounce}, spreading them out in a layer. Bring mixture to a boil, then lower heat and let simmer until sauce thickens and tortelloni are tender, ~{5-7%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> Add a splash of water if pan seems dry.

While tortelloni simmer, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @parmesan cheese{1/2%cup} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #small bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Remove pan from heat. Sprinkle panko crust mixture over tortelloni, covering them as evenly as possible.

Place pan under broiler (or in oven). Let broil (or bake) until crust is toasty and sauce is bubbly, ~{1-2%minutes}. Divide tortelloni between bowls and serve.